TL;DR:  We need to review all downstream changes to CAPBM

The metal3 community started the Cluster API provider project several years ago.  This project was introduced as a downstream openshift project shortly after.  It was called cluster-api-provider-baremetal.

The upstream and downstream projects continued to diverge until the upstream
project got rewritten using the new Cluster API.  It was then renamed to
cluster-api-provider-metal3.  The downstream project was never updated to this
new version and we continued to apply emergency patches to the old version.

Currently, openshift is interested in having a provider that can do CAPI.  We
created a new downstream project based on the upstream
cluster-api-provider-metal3.  In the future, we will want to deprecate
cluster-api-provider-baremetal.  But this project has accrued a lot of valuable
downstream-only fixes that we may wish to contribute upstream.

What are those fixes?

Let's do some git magic!

With our git remotes as:

{code:none}
capmb https://github.com/openshift/cluster-api-provider-baremetal
capm3 https://github.com/metal3-io/cluster-api-provider-metal3
{code}

We can ask for the closes common ancestor:

{code:none}
$ git merge-base upstream/main capbm/master
5676be29989f8b5f15130102442185f50028acf7
{code}

And then list all the merges (pull requests):

{code:none}
$ git log --oneline --merges --no-decorate 5676be29989f8b5f15130102442185f50028acf7..capbm/master | wc -l
143
{code}

We can ignore some early hacks and focus on features and bugs:

{code:none}
$ git log --oneline --merges --no-decorate 5676be29989f8b5f15130102442185f50028acf7..capbm/master | grep "Merge pull request" | wc -l
129
{code}

And maybe filter out robot PRs:

{code:none}
$ git log --oneline --merges --no-decorate 5676be29989f8b5f15130102442185f50028acf7..capbm/master | grep "Merge pull request" | grep -v "art-consistency" | wc -l
113
{code}

